args:
Cleo challenges Tartarus to single combat,
believing that she and her friends will take the
place of the hero. With the help of the reborn
Nidhogg, she defeats Tartarus and once more
vows to seek peace together with the prince.
You're all bark and no chomp! You'd better\nrun now if you know what's good for you!
And what would come of flight?
What meaning could there be in surviving\na world that tramples the soul of my liege\nunderfoot at every turn?
I shall destroy this world and\nrelease the soul of the king!
Gah, are you kidding me?! He ain't done?!
Beware. He grows ever more ferocious.
These Agito guys are a rash what won't\ngo away, but there's no doubtin' they're\nstrong as hell.
No, Cleo! You can't fight alone!
All will be well. I have to settle this.\nFor him...and for me.
One who has betrayed our king comes to\nplace her own neck upon the block?\nVery well.
We appear to be trapped in a space\nsomehow apart from the world!
You will remain and bear witness to\nCleo's judgment, just as you did when\nyou abandoned my liege.
Tartarus, I share your pain at losing\nHis Majesty...
But I believe that protecting the world he\nso loved will be what saves his soul.
Silence! You are a makeweight who knows\nnothing! What could you understand of\nHis Majesty's suffering?!
You claim this weak sham of a puppet will\nsave the world?! And that his so doing will\npermit our liege to rest easy?!
I don't mean that {player_name}\nwill save the world...
His Majesty was without peer, Tartarus,\nand there is no substitute for the hero.\nOn this, you are correct.
Then who, damn you?! Who will save this\nabominable world?!
But he will do it in conjunction with all of \nus who have gathered at the Halidom!
I know that even our combined might is no\nmatch for the heights of His Majesty.
We will run into hitches and discord,\nand in doing so realize our own weakness.

But no matter how many setbacks we 
endure, we will support one another and
continue to illuminate the world with the
light of hope!
I am proud to stand with all of them.
And it is why I will destroy you rather\nthan see you end this world!
(Are you watching this, Your Majesty?\nThis is my will to live on in the world\nyou've left behind.)
It's the Death's Reveler! But it looks\ndifferent from the way I know it...
...What?! Cleo, you had an audience with\nHis Majesty in this place?!
Tell me! What did he say?!\nWhat did he bid you do?!
Our conversation did not involve him\ndirecting me toward a particular course.
Instead, he had the compassion to make it\nso I could walk this world without him.
And now he will witness my determination\nfor himself!
Come, Death Reveler... Bear me unto\nmy liege...
My king eternal! My liege lord aeonian!\nI am now away to be at your side!
The ball of darkness has disappeared!\nI think we're free!
Damn, Cleo! Ya gave that guy a thumpin'\nfor the ages!
You clobbered Tartarus all by yourself!\nYou're like the grandmaster chef of\nfighting and junk!
For a part of me not having complete\nfaith in you.
Even though I swore to go from being a\nservant to being a comrade, my heart had\nclearly not made the full transition.
From this point forth, I would like to be\nincluded in your circle as a fellow seeker\nof peace.
I feel your determination, Cleo—and I\nvery much appreciate it.
She certainly has grown, hasn't she?\nTo think the reticent little servant would\ngo so far to prove herself!
Now, let's get some healing taken care of.\nZena, do you mind?
(Your Majesty, you truly are my guide\nin this world.)
(It may be dangerous, but I will walk on\nwith my own two feet. I swear it.)
Hey, guys! I think we're about halfway to\nthe bough that leads to the top!
HALF?! I hate this damn tree so much...
It seems we've still some time before we\narrive at the upper stratum.
Dim places like this ill suit me; I should\nvery much like to feel sun's kiss on my\nface once more.
Are you good to go, Cleo?
Yes, Zena has me back in tip-top shape.\nI'm sorry for the concern.
In that case, let's pick up the pace!
You could cut stone with that expression,\nGatov. Is aught amiss?
Only that for a moment I thought I felt\nsomeone nearby...
Oh? It's not like you to lose track of\nsomething like that once you've noticed it.
Well, it wasn't very definite. In any\ncase, let's just hurry on ahead.
